:"June 4, 1897, ch. 2","children":[],"tail":" (par. under “Soldiers’ Home, District of Columbia”), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/30/54"},"text":"30 Stat. 54","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-06-28/ch383/s402/d"},"text":"June 28, 1950, ch. 383, § 402(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/272"},"text":"64 Stat. 272","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a) the words “an officer of the Medical Corps” are substituted for the words “medical officer”. The words “on active duty” are inserted for clarity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b) the words “rates of charge”, “to cover the cost of purchase, inspection, and so forth”, and “as can be spared without detriment to the military service” are omitted as surplusage. The words “the contract prices paid therefor” are omitted to reflect Title IV of the National Security Act of 1947, as amended (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/585"},"text":"63 Stat. 585","children":[],"tail":"), which authorized the Secretary of Defense to prescribe regulations governing the use and sale of certain inventories at cost including applicable administrative expenses. (See opinion of the Assistant General Counsel (Fiscal Matters) of the Office of the Secretary of Defense, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-01-04"},"text":"January 4, 1955","children":[],"tail":".) The word “equipments” is omitted as covered by the word “supplies”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “in the District of Columbia” are omitted as surplusage, since there is only one Soldiers’ Home. The words “Upon proper application therefor” are omitted as surplusage. The words “its contract prices” are omitted to reflect Title IV of the National Security Act of 1947, as amended (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/585"},"text":"63 Stat. 585","children":[],"tail":"), which authorized the Secretary of Defense to prescribe regulations governing the use and sale of certain inventories at cost, including applicable administrative expenses. (See opinion of the Assistant General Counsel (Fiscal Matters) of the Office of the Secretary of Defense, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-01-04"},"text":"January 4, 1955","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaafb1ba9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idaafb1baa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 7624, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/473"},"text":"70A Stat. 473","children":[],"tail":", related to reports to Congress with respect to amounts paid or received under prior sections 7622 and 7623 (now 8822 and 8823) of this title, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/533/s1/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–533, § 1(10)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/247"},"text":"74 Stat. 247","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaafb1bab-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"